{
  "article_id": "Oregonian1901",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "An air of mystery pervades each of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the little islands",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in the scant archipelago off ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast of California.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Clemente Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scl",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is strewn with enormous prehistoric mortars and pestles, and here and there are numerous evidences that ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a giant race",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " lived there before the Portuguese navigator, ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Cabrillo",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "jca",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", sailed for conquest up the coast of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Alta California",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_local",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in 1542. ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is indented by many strange caves, weird grottoes, where one may see remains of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a race of fishers and artisans",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " with shells. ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " has been the scene of titanic erosions by ice, water and sand. The grotesque pillars that lift themselves above the island level, the winding caves that twist from the shores into the heart of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and the roaring gulches and canyons denote a spot rich in possibilities for both scientist and dreamer. ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is used as a pasturage for thousands of sheep, and it, too, is full of absorbing interest regarding extinct races of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "aborigines",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_chumash",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The Smithsonian Institution scientists have gathered tons of stone, shell and bone utensils and personal ornaments from ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}